rComments: Very dry professor. Not that interesting, she's just there. Fair marker. Could have done without her course.

I've taken two courses that she taught. She's really into students' discussion so she usually gives out general ideas and then asks for students' opinion or brainstorming. That's why she has participation graded. ALWAYS come to class and read the books prior to lecture. Her tone and vocal could be very professional and some people may be bored.
Prof was very monotone. Her slides just consist of background history and useless images. Hard marker, worst English class I have ever taken.
Great Prof. Book selection was really interesting, I learned a lot from this class. Do the readings, go to office hours, speak in class and you will do well.

Ella is one of the most intelligent and articulate profs I've had. Her course is demanding and if you don't do the readings then you're screwed, but if you come prepared and participate then her classes are extremely rewarding. High standards, but fair marker.
Good prof, good lecturer, no complaints really but all ENG courses are subjective and so not easy to get 80s/90s. Wouldn't recommend it as a GPA booster but interesting prof/course overall.
